China National Chemical Corporation
 









Officers and directors


Ren Jianxin
President


Ross Macallister
CIO


Address
62 Beisihuan Xilu, Haidian DistrictBeijing, BeijingCHN+86 10 8267 7530 (Phone)+86-1082677088 (Fax)








If it's a product of the downstream chemical manufacturing process, then state-owned China National Chemical Corporation probably makes it. The company, among China's largest industrial firms, is known as ChemChina, and is divided itself into six units. The largest is Advanced Materials & Specialty Chemicals, followed by Chlor-alkali & Basic Chemical Products, and Agrochemicals. ChemChina also refines petroleum, manufactures rubber and silicone products, and manufactures specialty chemicals. The company operates in 140 countries worldwide. In 2017 ChemChina acquired Switzerland-based Syngenta for $43 billion.


