Share








Things 
 to Know About ChemChina


Swiss pesticide and seed giant Syngenta has agreed to a $43 billion takeover offer from China National Chemical, in the most ambitious foreign takeover attempt by a Chinese company to date. Here are five things to know about the company commonly known as ChemChina.

3 Feb 2016 5:17am

By
Wayne Ma








1
What is ChemChina?
Share on Twitter





China National Chemical Corp. was formed in 2004 and is the largest chemicals company in China. Headquartered in Beijing, ChemChina remains unlisted and is a state-owned enterprise ultimately managed by the Chinese government. ChemChina’s revenue last year was $45 billion and it employs 140,000 people, according to its website.



140,000

                                       The number of people ChemChina says it employs.


                                    









 







2
What does it do?
Share on Twitter





ChemChina produces a wide array of chemicals and is also a leading manufacturer of tires, conveyor belts and chemical machinery. The company is China’s largest producer of pesticides and its chief mandate is to improve the protection of Chinese crops. The company operates nine crude-oil refineries in China, but also owns the popular Malan Noodle fast-food restaurant chain. 
















3
Who leads the company?
Share on Twitter





ChemChina’s founder and chairman is 58-year-old Ren Jianxin. Mr. Ren was born in northwestern China, studied chemical engineering and has a graduate degree in economics. He founded his first company, Bluestar, in 1984 with loan of less than $5,000 and presided over its expansion from an industrial-cleaning company to a chemicals conglomerate, acquiring more than 100 state-owned Chinese chemicals companies. It later merged with other businesses affiliated with China’s chemicals ministry and Mr. Ren was named head of the state-owned behemoth. 






                                                Agence France-Presse/Getty Images
                                             











4
What has the company been buying?
Share on Twitter





Since 2006, ChemChina has spent billions of dollars on overseas acquisitions in countries including France, Italy, Germany, Israel and the U.K. Its more notable acquisitions include Italian tire maker Pirelli, which it bought for about $7.7 billion last year, and Israel’s Makhteshim Agan Group, the world’s largest maker of generic pesticides, for about $2.4 billion in 2011. Other acquisitions include France’s Adisseo Group and Rhodia, makers of animal feed and organic silicon, respectively, and KraussMaffei Group, a German company that makes equipment to process plastics and rubber.






                                                Getty Images
                                             











5
Why does it want Syngenta?
Share on Twitter





ChemChina says it wants to grow Syngenta’s business in China and other emerging markets, but it may also have an eye on the pesticide and seed giant’s significant foothold in the U.S. Acquiring Syngenta’s intellectual property is also attractive, as the Swiss company develops genetically engineered seeds that may help further open the tightly-regulated Chinese market for biotech crops.






                                                Agence France-Presse/Getty Images
                                             












More
                  5 Things
            

















































China National Chemical Corporation: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 2:24 AM ET
Chemicals

Company Overview of China National Chemical Corporation



Snapshot People




Company Overview
China National Chemical Corporation, through its subsidiaries, manufactures chemical products. The company offers chemical materials and specialty chemical products that include organo-silicon, silicon alloy, organo-fluorine, polyurethane, and engineering plastics, as well as high performance fibers, general plastics and rubbers, and animal nutrition chemical products. It also provides basic chemical products that comprise salt and coal chemicals, minerals, and mineral basic chemicals; oil processing and refining products, such as energy and petrochemical products; agrochemicals, which include chemical fertilizers and pesticides; and rubber products, including auto tire, non-tire rubber, spe...
China National Chemical Corporation, through its subsidiaries, manufactures chemical products. The company offers chemical materials and specialty chemical products that include organo-silicon, silicon alloy, organo-fluorine, polyurethane, and engineering plastics, as well as high performance fibers, general plastics and rubbers, and animal nutrition chemical products. It also provides basic chemical products that comprise salt and coal chemicals, minerals, and mineral basic chemicals; oil processing and refining products, such as energy and petrochemical products; agrochemicals, which include chemical fertilizers and pesticides; and rubber products, including auto tire, non-tire rubber, special tire, and latex products. In addition, the company offers chemical equipment that include ionic membrane electrolyzers, rubber machinery, drying equipment, and axle gears; and consulting services. It serves customers in China and internationally. China National Chemical Corporation is based in Beijing, China.
Detailed Description


